  "notes": "Latgalian (latgaļu volūda), an Eastern Baltic variety of Latvia recognised as a protected historic variant of Latvian; treated as a separate language by ISO 639-3 (ltg) and Glottolog. The 2007 standard orthography (Latgalian Orthography Rules, approved by the State Language Centre) is close to phonemic, with macrons for long vowels (ā ē ī ō ū), hooks/cedillas for palatalised ģ ķ ļ ņ, hačeks for č š ž, and — unlike standard Latvian — the letter ⟨y⟩ for the central vowel /ɨ/. Diphthongs /iɛ/ and /uɔ/ are written ⟨ie⟩ and ⟨uo⟩. Pitch accent and vowel-length interactions are not modelled here; stress is generally on the first syllable.",
